(150, '_transient_dash_de3249c4736ad3bd2cd29147c4a0d43e', '<h4>Plugins recientes</h4>\n<h5><a href=''http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/scheduled-post-unstick/''>Scheduled Post Unstick</a></h5>&nbsp;<span>(<a href=''plugin-install.php?tab=plugin-information&amp;plugin=scheduled-post-unstick&amp;_wpnonce=2022d2aa3a&amp;TB_iframe=true&amp;width=600&amp;height=800'' class=''thickbox'' title=''Scheduled Post Unstick''>Instalar</a>)</span>\n<p>This plugin allows you to schedule to unstick a post on a specific date and time.\n\nIt is available in:\n\n German\n English</p>\n', 'no'),
(151, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://markjaquith.wordpress.com/2012/07/17/wp-help-one-dot-oh/'' title=''My WP Help plugin just got a huge update. Version 1.0 is really worth checking out. I’m quite proud of it. WP Help WP Help is a plugin for creating documentation for display within the WordPress admin. Many WordPress installs are customized, and it’s really helpful to have a centralized resource for documenting those features. You can create documents about  [&hellip;]''>Mark Jaquith: WP Help 1.0</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/7NXPEcJbDwA/'' title=''Sure, folks blog for many things, but that usually boils down into two main categories, personal reasons or business reasons. We’d love to hear what you blog for and why, and your answers may just appear in a future post. Don’t forget to vote and leave a comment below! View This Pollonline survey [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: What do you blog for?</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/RCefz1lSw2g/'' title=''The latest free WordPress eBook from Code Poet has arrived, Locking Down WordPress. This new eBook from Rachel Baker, Brad Williams, and John Ford, will show you how to secure your WordPress installation and take care of it when things get out of hand. Security should be one of your fore-most concerns with any website, and this eBook is free and available in [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: Free eBook: Locking Down WordPress</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2012/07/digg-wasnt-a-failure/'' title=''Thumbs Up: Digg Wasn’t A Failure, It Was A Beginning, by Aubrey Sabala. [&hellip;]''>Matt: Digg Wasn’t A Failure</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2012/07/art-apple-secret-service/'' title=''When Art, Apple and the Secret Service Collide: ‘People Staring at Computers’. Great read. [&hellip;]''>Matt: Art, Apple, Secret Service</a></li></ul></div>', 'no');

